  "content": "The Reactor sits in the Data Infrastructure Layer and serves as the primary storage node for documents and files. It supports multiple storage adapters for various environments -- local, cloud, and decentralized storage networks like Ceramic or IPFS. Alongside the Reactor, Powerhouse Network Components provide services required to build scalable networks of Reactor nodes: event buses, queues, caching services, and load balancers.",
